Assets Goodwill And Intangible Assets Other GRF300 Amount

This is the value, as at the relevant date, of the component of other equity investments which are purchased goodwill and other intangible assets. Equity securities are, as defined by the Australian Accounting Standards, contracts that evidence a residual interest in the assets of an entity after deducting all its liabilities. This includes equity securities lent or sold by the entity under repurchase agreements, where the transaction does not result in the transfer of the rights of ownership of the securities away from the entity to another party.
Assets Limited Recourse Borrowing Amount
The value of limited recourse borrowing arrangements (which includes instalment warrants) that the Self Managed Superannuation Fund (SMSF) entered into inside Australia.
Assets Net Tangible Assets Other GRF300 Amount

This is the value, as at the relevant date, of the component of other equity investments which are not purchased goodwill and other intangible assets. Equity securities are, as defined by the Australian Accounting Standards, contracts that evidence a residual interest in the assets of an entity after deducting all its liabilities. This includes equity securities lent or sold by the entity under repurchase agreements, where the transaction does not result in the transfer of the rights of ownership of the securities away from the entity to another party.
